## Cloud Deployment

### Azure App Service

**1. Install Azure CLI:**
```bash
# Linux/macOS
curl -sL https://aka.ms/InstallAzureCLIDeb | sudo bash

# Windows
winget install Microsoft.AzureCLI
```

**2. Login:**
```bash
az login
```

**3. Create resources:**
```bash
az group create --name {{ProjectName}}RG --location eastus

az appservice plan create \
  --name {{ProjectName}}Plan \
  --resource-group {{ProjectName}}RG \
  --sku B1 \
  --is-linux

az webapp create \
  --name {{ProjectName}}App \
  --resource-group {{ProjectName}}RG \
  --plan {{ProjectName}}Plan \
  --runtime "DOTNETCORE:9.0"
```

**4. Deploy:**
```bash
cd src
dotnet publish -c Release -o ./publish

az webapp deployment source config-zip \
  --resource-group {{ProjectName}}RG \
  --name {{ProjectName}}App \
  --src ./publish.zip
```

**5. Configure database:**

For production, use Azure SQL Database instead of SQLite:

```bash
az sql server create \
  --name {{ProjectNameLower}}server \
  --resource-group {{ProjectName}}RG \
  --location eastus \
  --admin-user sqladmin \
  --admin-password YourSecurePassword123!

az sql db create \
  --resource-group {{ProjectName}}RG \
  --server {{ProjectNameLower}}server \
  --name {{ProjectName}}DB \
  --service-objective S0

# Get connection string
az sql db show-connection-string \
  --client ado.net \
  --server {{ProjectNameLower}}server \
  --name {{ProjectName}}DB
```

**6. Set connection string in App Service:**
```bash
az webapp config connection-string set \
  --name {{ProjectName}}App \
  --resource-group {{ProjectName}}RG \
  --connection-string-type SQLAzure \
  --settings DefaultConnection="<connection-string>"
```

### AWS Elastic Beanstalk

**1. Install EB CLI:**
```bash
pip install awsebcli
```

**2. Initialize:**
```bash
cd src
eb init -p "64bit Amazon Linux 2023 v3.0.0 running .NET 9" {{ProjectName}}
```

**3. Create environment:**
```bash
eb create {{ProjectNameLower}}-prod
```

**4. Deploy:**
```bash
dotnet publish -c Release -o ./publish
cd publish
zip -r ../deploy.zip .
cd ..
eb deploy
```

**5. Configure database:**

Use Amazon RDS PostgreSQL:

```bash
# Create RDS instance
aws rds create-db-instance \
  --db-instance-identifier {{ProjectNameLower}}db \
  --db-instance-class db.t3.micro \
  --engine postgres \
  --master-username dbadmin \
  --master-user-password YourSecurePassword123! \
  --allocated-storage 20

# Set environment variable
eb setenv ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection="Host=<rds-endpoint>;Database={{ProjectName}};Username=dbadmin;Password=YourSecurePassword123!"
```

### Google Cloud Run

**1. Install gcloud CLI:**
```bash
curl https://sdk.cloud.google.com | bash
gcloud init
```

**2. Build container:**
```bash
gcloud builds submit --tag gcr.io/YOUR_PROJECT_ID/{{ProjectNameLower}}
```

**3. Deploy:**
```bash
gcloud run deploy {{ProjectNameLower}} \
  --image gcr.io/YOUR_PROJECT_ID/{{ProjectNameLower}} \
  --platform managed \
  --region us-central1 \
  --allow-unauthenticated
```

**4. Configure Cloud SQL (PostgreSQL):**
```bash
gcloud sql instances create {{ProjectNameLower}}db \
  --database-version=POSTGRES_15 \
  --tier=db-f1-micro \
  --region=us-central1

gcloud sql databases create {{ProjectName}} \
  --instance={{ProjectNameLower}}db

gcloud run services update {{ProjectNameLower}} \
  --add-cloudsql-instances YOUR_PROJECT_ID:us-central1:{{ProjectNameLower}}db \
  --set-env-vars ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection="Host=/cloudsql/YOUR_PROJECT_ID:us-central1:{{ProjectNameLower}}db;Database={{ProjectName}};Username=postgres;Password=yourpassword"
```

### DigitalOcean App Platform

**1. Create `app.yaml`:**
```yaml
name: {{ProjectNameLower}}
services:
  - name: web
    source_dir: /
    dockerfile_path: Dockerfile
    http_port: 8080
    routes:
      - path: /
    health_check:
      http_path: /health
    envs:
      - key: ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT
        value: Production
      - key: ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection
        value: ${db.DATABASE_URL}
databases:
  - name: db
    engine: PG
    version: "15"
```

**2. Deploy via CLI:**
```bash
doctl apps create --spec app.yaml
```

Or connect GitHub repository via DigitalOcean dashboard.

