## Security Checklist

- [ ] Remove development event dashboard in production (`/_swap/dev/events`)
- [ ] Enable HTTPS redirect
- [ ] Use environment variables for secrets
- [ ] Enable CORS only for trusted origins
- [ ] Add request rate limiting
- [ ] Enable HSTS header
- [ ] Use parameterized SQL queries (already done via EF Core)
- [ ] Sanitize user inputs (already done via model binding)
- [ ] Keep dependencies updated (`dotnet list package --outdated`)

**Production Program.cs hardening:**

```csharp
if (!app.Environment.IsDevelopment())
{
    app.UseHsts();
    app.UseHttpsRedirection();
    
    // Remove dev dashboard
    // app.MapSwapDevDashboard(); // Comment out
}

app.UseCors(policy => policy
    .WithOrigins("https://yourdomain.com")
    .AllowAnyMethod()
    .AllowAnyHeader());
```

